// 2. Locate each INSERTION POINT marker below.
// 3. Insert the block ABOVE the identified code.
// 4. Do not remove any existing code.
// 5. After applying, run runtime validation.
//
// VALIDATION
// ==========
// Success: No behavioral change. Runtime behavior identical to pre-patch.
// Failure: Any behavioral change whatsoever.
// =============================================================================


// =============================================================================
// INSERTION POINT 1: TOP OF FILE (replaces or precedes existing header)
// =============================================================================
// Replace the existing L1 header block (or prepend if no header exists) with:

/*
 * =============================================================================
 * SVARTÚLFRVERSE | ENGINE CORE
 * =============================================================================
 *
 * Layer:       En_ (Engine Layer)
 * File:        En_Core.js
 * Role:        Runtime orchestration authority
 *
 * This file is the invisible operating system of the SvartúlfrVerse.
 * It is not a Character, not a World, and not an Experience.
 * It exists solely to maintain consistency between all other layers.
 *
 * RESPONSIBILITIES
 * ----------------
 * - World routing and dimension activation
 * - Runtime state management (session variables, context)
 * - POV Override Firewall (canonical casting enforcement)
 * - Lorebook compilation (priority, trigger, apply budget)
 * - Output standardization (header formatting, HUD injection)
 *
 * SEMANTIC LAYERS ORCHESTRATED
 * -----------------------------
 * En_  (Engine)     — This file. Runtime logic, routing, enforcement.
 * W_   (World)      — Factual world knowledge. Geography, culture, lore.
 * C_   (Character)  — Factual character knowledge. Identity, appearance, traits.
 * Ex_  (Experience) — Deployable product. Scenario, cast, POV configuration.
 *
 * LAYER DEPENDENCIES (one-way, strictly enforced)
 * ------------------------------------------------
 * En_
 *  └── W_
 *       └── C_
 *            └── Ex_
 *
 * Experiences compose Worlds and Characters.
 * Worlds and Characters never depend on Experiences.
 *
 * GOVERNANCE HIERARCHY
 * --------------------
 * 1. Observed Runtime Behavior  (highest authority)
 * 2. Architecture Decision Records (ADR)
 * 3. Workflow Definitions
 * 4. This Documentation
 *
 * If runtime behavior contradicts this file, UPDATE THIS FILE.
 * Never force runtime to match documentation.
 *
 * LEGACY NAMING NOTE
 * ------------------
 * This file was authored during the L1/L2/L3 era.
 * The following mapping applies throughout the codebase:
 *   L1  →  En_  (Engine Layer)
 *   L2  →  W_   (World Layer)
 *   L3  →  C_   (Character Layer)
 *   --  →  Ex_  (Experience Layer — added post-migration)
 *
 * Legacy variable names (mvL0.dimensions, mvL0.dimensionAliases) remain
 * active for backward compatibility. See DEBT-001 in Technical Debt Report.
 *
 * RUNTIME ENVIRONMENT
 * -------------------
 * JanitorAI ES5 sandbox.
 * Permitted: var, for loops, indexOf, Math, new Date, regex.
 * Forbidden: let, const, =>, .includes(), .map(), .filter(), try/catch.
 *
 * Message Depth: 10 (maximum persistence — engine must remain active).
 *
